OL,3,CHow Reeves has found an additional
OL,4,C#50bn a year to borrow
OL,6,FTogether they represent the biggest
OL,7,Fshare of increase in the Treasury's
OL,8,Fcapacity to borrow every year to the
OL,9,Ftune of between #50bn and #60bn,
OL,10,Faccording to the Resolution Foundation
OL,11,Fand the Institute of Fiscal Studies.
OL,13,FThese are big bucks. And what matters
OL,14,Fis that this is quite literally magic
OL,15,Fmoney. It is a different way of seeing
OL,16,Fthe government's liabilities, but the
OL,17,Fliabilities are in all economic
OL,18,Freality unchanged.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
