OL,3,CHow Reeves has found an additional
OL,4,C#50bn a year to borrow
OL,6,FIt creates space for investment, but
OL,7,Fconstrained space. As I said at the
OL,8,Fstart, moving to snuffle gives the
OL,9,Fchancellor the means to begin the
OL,10,Freversal of decades of too-low public
OL,11,Fsector investment. But the recovery
OL,12,Fwon't happen overnight.
OL,14,FShe won't have a bottomless purse, and
OL,15,Fbecause of her second fiscal
OL,16,Fconstraint, that current spending must
OL,17,Fin time only be funded by taxation
OL,18,F(probably by the fifth year of the
OL,19,Ffiscal forecast).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
